Dexter Fletcher, David O'Hara, Deborah Unger, Ashley Taylor. Directed by Bronwen Hughes.(n)

programme.title: Hickok
programme.desc: Looking to start a new life for himself in rural Kansas, the infamous gunslinger Wild Bill Hickok is soon tested by a band of seedy outlaws who challenge his authority and threaten his new start in this ction-packed Western. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: A Room With a View
programme.desc: While visiting Florence, repressed and proper Lucy meets and falls for the charming and free-spirited George. Based on the novel by E. M. Forster. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Morning Glory
programme.desc: A news producer hopes to end the feud between an anchorman and his cohost in a last-ditch effort to save their failing morning show. in this hilarious glimpse at the world of live television. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Libeled Lady
programme.desc: Screwball-comedy classic that was nominated for a Best Picture Oscar chronicles the misadventures of a cutthroat newspaper editor whose scheme to prevent a libel suit ends up exploding in his face as well as all those involved. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Dead Heat on a Merry-Go-Round
programme.desc: The escapades of a zestful con man provide entertaining fun in this clever comedy-melodrama. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: 23 Paces to Baker Street
programme.desc: Blind writer tries to solve a London kidnap-murder case. Superior, well-acted thriller. Good mood, suspense and atmosphere. Holds interest to the end. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Last of Sheila
programme.desc: A filmmaker invites six movie-business types on a weeklong yacht voyage on the Mediterranean, where they engage in a role-playing game that turns murderous. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Silent Fall
programme.desc: An autistic 9-year-old witnesses his parents' murder. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Primal Fear
programme.desc: Richard Gere and Oscar nominee Edward Norton star in this intense courtroom drama. Gere plays slick lawyer Martin Vail, who agrees to defend a guileless 19-year-old (Norton) who has been accused in the brutal murder of the Archbishop of Chicago. Though Vail sees the case as a way to gain publicity, the revelations in the case begin to chill him. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Ninth Configuration
programme.desc: An army psychiatrist whose own sanity is questionable arrives at a detention center for AWOL soldiers to start a new job. Adapted by director William Peter Blatty from his novel "Twinkle, Twinkle, Killer Kane." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Black Moon Rising
programme.desc: A thief (Tommy Lee Jones) searches for a stolen supercar that contains his stashed goods. Linda Hamilton, Robert Vaughn. Earl: Richard Jaeckel. Ringer: Lee Ving. Johnson: Bubba Smith. Billy: Dan Shor. Directed by Harley Cokliss. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cause for Alarm
programme.desc: A letter incriminates a widow, whose dead husband wrote it when he suspected her of plotting to kill him. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: High Wall
programme.desc: A World War II veteran suffering from a recurring brain injury teams with a woman psychiatrist to prove himself innocent of his wife's murder. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Wrong Man
programme.desc: A different kind of Alfred Hitchcock film: a fact-based, semi-documentary account of a New York City musician who is falsely accused of an armed robbery and the nightmarish impact it has on him and his family, especially his mentally unstable wife. The idea for the motion picture came when Hitchcock read about the miscarriage of justice in a Life magazine article. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Murder Is My Beat
programme.desc: A detective (Paul Langton) arrests a singer (Barbara Payton) for murder but begins to believe she is innocent. Mrs. Abbott: Selena Royle. Hawley: Robert Shayne. Abbott: Roy Gordon. Edgar G. Ulmer directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Moontide
programme.desc: Story of a barge worker's (Jean Gabin) romance with a waitress (Ida Lupino). Thomas Mitchell is the blackmailer who taunts them. Nutsy: Claude Rains. Brothers: Jerome Cowan. Woman on Boat: Helene Reynolds. Effective script by John O'Hara, from the novel by Willard Robertson. Realistic. Archie Mayo, Fritz Lang directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Tokyo Joe
programme.desc: Humphrey Bogart as an ex-serviceman and war hero in postwar Tokyo, where he gets blackmailed by a Japanese royal into participating in a plot to smuggle war criminals back into the country. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Sirocco
programme.desc: A Damascus casino operator runs afoul of his allies when he runs guns to the insurrectionists who are attempting to overthrow the local French protectorate. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: PL Stories: Jarred Gillett
programme.desc: Jarred Gillett made history earlier this year when he became the first Premier League referee ever to be fitted with a special head-mounted camera during Crystal Palace’s home victory over Manchester United. PL Stories is granted exclusive access to Gillet and his officiating team on matchday, offering fans a unique insight into refereeing at the highest level. Premier League match officials and in particular referees are often the most scrutinised individuals in the game and this show reveals how difficult a task they have.(n)
